The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) and presidential aspirant for the 2023 general elections, Bola Ahmed Tinubu has been a regular on social media trends since he announced his intentions in January.
The politician is again topping Twitter trends this week for comments attributed to him from his visit to Oba Lamidi Adeyemi, Alaafin of Oyo and the Olubadan-elect, Chief Lekan Balogun.
Over the weekend, Bola Tinubu reacted to concerns raised by some critics that Nigeria deserves a youthful leader at the helm of affairs. “You will grow old, you will become president but I will become president first,” the presidential aspirant responded to his critics.
In another comment attributed to him, Tinubu is quoted as saying he  is willing to dirty himself to fulfil his lifelong ambit on of becoming president.
 
